\caption{\label{A120} JGNRs A120 subtypes. Ribbons shown on a), b), c) are symmetric, because their opposite edges highlighted by red (top) and blue (bottom) can be superimposed by simple translation, e.g. they have inversion centres like $I_1$,$I_2$ in Fig.\ref{Characteristic_vectors}. Ribbons depicted on d), e), f) are asymmetric due to different sorts of their opposite edges. Only a) and f) ribbons can be smoothly rolled into a nanotube. The framed ribbon is of the same A120 type as the one shown in Fig.\ref{JGNR types} d).}
\end{figure*}

